0. Install kvm kit, thin-provisioning-tools
1. Set up a VM with leap 42.3 or some other suitable distro, to act as a kiwi runner
2. Set up a logical volume, "ci-root", of 5GB or more and expose it to kiwirunner VM (virt, raw-backed vmdk etc)
3. Check that TARGET in rebuild-ci-root.sh makes sense in the kiwirunner VM
4. Run rebuild-ci-root.sh in the kiwirunner VM (and power it off if virtualbox)
5. Check that VG in buildit.sh makes sense
6. Run buildit.sh
